{% layout 'theme' %}

<style>
  .hh-page { background:#080808; color:#f2ede1; font-family:'Montserrat',sans-serif; min-height:60vh; }
  .hh-page-inner { max-width:780px; margin:0 auto; padding:80px 48px; }
  .hh-page h1 { font-family:'Playfair Display',serif; font-size:42px; font-weight:400; color:#f2ede1; margin-bottom:12px; }
  .hh-page-rule { width:48px; height:1px; background:#C4A843; margin-bottom:48px; }
  .hh-page h2 { font-family:'Playfair Display',serif; font-size:22px; font-weight:400; color:#f2ede1; margin:40px 0 16px; }
  .hh-page p { font-size:13px; color:rgba(242,237,225,0.55); line-height:1.9; font-weight:300; margin-bottom:16px; }
  .hh-size-table { width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin-bottom:32px; }
  .hh-size-table th { font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.15em; color:#C4A843; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:700; padding:12px 0; border-bottom:1px solid #2a2218; text-align:left; }
  .hh-size-table td { font-size:13px; color:rgba(242,237,225,0.55); font-weight:300; padding:14px 0; border-bottom:1px solid #1a1510; }
  @media(max-width:768px){ .hh-page-inner{ padding:56px 24px; } .hh-page h1{ font-size:32px; } }
</style>

<div class="hh-page">
  <div class="hh-page-inner">
    <h1>Size Guide</h1>
    <div class="hh-page-rule"></div>

    <p>Finding the right fit makes all the difference. Use the guides below to measure at home before ordering.</p>

    <h2>Ring Sizes</h2>
    <p>To measure your ring size, wrap a thin strip of paper around your finger, mark where it overlaps, and measure the length in millimeters. Match to the chart below.</p>
    <table class="hh-size-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>US Size</th><th>Circumference (mm)</th><th>Diameter (mm)</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>5</td><td>49.3</td><td>15.7</td></tr>
        <tr><td>6</td><td>51.9</td><td>16.5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>7</td><td>54.4</td><td>17.3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>8</td><td>57.0</td><td>18.1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>9</td><td>59.5</td><td>18.9</td></tr>
        <tr><td>10</td><td>62.1</td><td>19.8</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Bracelet Sizes</h2>
    <p>Measure your wrist with a flexible tape measure or a strip of paper. Add 0.5&ndash;1 inch for a comfortable fit.</p>
    <table class="hh-size-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Size</th><th>Wrist Circumference</th><th>Bracelet Length</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>XS / S</td><td>Up to 6 in (15.2 cm)</td><td>6.5 in (16.5 cm)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>M</td><td>6&ndash;7 in (15.2&ndash;17.8 cm)</td><td>7 in (17.8 cm)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L / XL</td><td>7+ in (17.8+ cm)</td><td>7.5 in (19 cm)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Necklace Lengths</h2>
    <table class="hh-size-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Length</th><th>Style / Placement</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>14 in (35.5 cm)</td><td>Choker — sits at the base of the neck</td></tr>
        <tr><td>16 in (40.6 cm)</td><td>Collar — rests just below collarbone</td></tr>
        <tr><td>18 in (45.7 cm)</td><td>Princess — classic length, most popular</td></tr>
        <tr><td>20 in (50.8 cm)</td><td>Matinee — sits at top of bust</td></tr>
        <tr><td>24 in (61 cm)</td><td>Opera — falls to bust or below</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>All our necklaces come with an adjustable chain that allows for 2-inch flexibility for a customizable fit.</p>
  </div>
</div>
